# CODEOWNERS — ScamReport
#
# Auto-routes review requests when a PR touches a path. Last-matching rule
# wins per path. Tied to the team mapping locked on 2026-04-28 (see
# `docs/sprint-2.md` and the term-assignment delivery plan).
#
# NOTE: GitHub usernames here are placeholders matching team initials.
# A.P (Orchestrator + Infra) must replace each `@A.P`/`@T.P`/etc. with the
# actual GitHub login before merging this file. Until then, GitHub will warn
# that the owners do not match real users; reviews still get routed manually.

# Default — A.P approves anything not otherwise matched.
*                                       @A.P

# Backend / contract / DB — T.P + S.P co-own; A.P backstop.
apps/api/**                             @T.P @S.P @A.P
packages/shared/**                      @T.P @S.P @A.P
prisma/**                               @T.P @S.P @A.P

# Mobile — Y.R + B.S co-own; A.P backstop.
apps/mobile/**                          @Y.R @B.S @A.P

# Tests — S.P (integration owner) signs off in addition to area owners.
**/*.test.ts                            @S.P
**/*_test.dart                          @S.P
apps/mobile/integration_test/**         @S.P
apps/mobile/test/**                     @S.P
apps/api/test/**                        @S.P

# Infra / security / docs — A.P. Security-touching files also pull in S.P.
.github/**                              @A.P
firestore.rules                         @A.P @S.P
firebase.json                           @A.P
firestore.indexes.json                  @A.P
.claude/**                              @A.P
docs/**                                 @A.P
CODEOWNERS                              @A.P
PRODUCT-REQUIREMENTS.md                 @A.P
DATABASE_DESIGN.md                      @A.P @T.P @S.P
SECURITY.md                             @A.P @S.P
